node.text:
In 2015 we set out to tell stories about the people and places that inspired us as a brand. In lieu of traditional advertising, we poured our hearts into making a whole series of character-driven films that would eventually be known as YETI Presents.

Now six years later, with roughly 85 YETI Presents films completed, we’d like to tip our hat to one of the early greats that started it off: Cosmo.

Thank you all for sharing your stories, watching ours, and for helping to make YETI a community. It’s been a wild ride, here’s to what’s next.

@alphonsefishingco

For the past 15 years, YETI coolers have been built upon unsurpassed thermal regulation and durability. Take a trip down memory lane with us and YETI co-founder, Roy Seiders in one of our first ads for the original Tundra.

This week we're turning back the clock to 2006 when it all began. Celebrate 15 Years of Cold with us as we share some of your favorite YETI videos and moments from the archives.

Before the tag line “Built for the Wild”, we used “Wildly Stronger! Keep Ice Longer!” And before we had a team of hunting ambassadors, there was living legend Jim Shockey. He’s one of the most accomplished and traveled adventure hunters alive today, and we wouldn’t be where we are without him blazing the trail with us. @jimshockeyofficial

node.text:
In 2015 we set out to tell stories about the people and places that inspired us as a brand. In lieu of traditional advertising, we poured our hearts into making a whole series of character-driven films that would eventually be known as YETI Presents.

Now six years later, with roughly 85 YETI Presents films completed, we’d like to tip our hat to one of the early greats that started it off: Cosmo.

Thank you all for sharing your stories, watching ours, and for helping to make YETI a community. It’s been a wild ride, here’s to what’s next.

@alphonsefishingco

Since we started building coolers in the early 2000s, we’ve put our Tundras through a great deal of testing to prove they are built for the wild. In 2011, we felt one more test was needed: the grizzly test. 
 
Our Tundra Hard Coolers have been thoroughly tested by the Interagency Grizzly Bear Committee (IGBC) in both controlled simulations and with wild grizzly bears. In addition to partnering with us on this video, the IGBC officially approved the YETI Tundra Hard Coolers for use on public lands occupied by grizzlies. 
 
Continue celebrating 15 Years of Cold with us as we share some of your favorite YETI videos and moments from the archives.

For the past 15 years, YETI coolers have been built upon unsurpassed thermal regulation and durability. Take a trip down memory lane with us and YETI co-founder, Roy Seiders in one of our first ads for the original Tundra.

This week we're turning back the clock to 2006 when it all began. Celebrate 15 Years of Cold with us as we share some of your favorite YETI videos and moments from the archives.

node.text:
“In 2006, we founded YETI Coolers with a simple mission: build the cooler we’d use every day if it existed. One that could take the abuse we knew we’d put it through out in the field and on the water. One that simply wouldn’t break.” - Roy and Ryan Seiders, YETI Founders

For 15 years, YETI products have performed when it matters most - whether that be an excursion into the remote Alaskan wilderness, chasing redfish on the Gulf coast, or just getting together with friends in the backyard.

This week we're turning back the clock to 2006 when it all began. Celebrate 15 Years of Cold with us as we share some of your favorite YETI videos and moments from the archives.
